<mixertitle>Search the <mixer var="GAP"/> web site</mixertitle>

<hr/>
<p>You can use Google to search within the complete GAP website, manuals of GAP and packages, and GAP Forum archives.</p>

<ul>
<li><a href="https://www.google.co.uk/search?q=site%3Awww.gap-system.org%3A">Complete GAP website (including manuals)</a></li>
<li><a href="https://www.google.co.uk/search?q=site%3Awww.gap-system.org/Manuals/%3A">Manuals of GAP and packages</a></li>
<li><a href="https://www.google.co.uk/search?q=site%3Ahttp://mail.gap-system.org/pipermail/forum/%3A">GAP Forum Archives since December 2003</a></li>
<li><a href="https://www.google.co.uk/search?q=site%3Awww.gap-system.org/ForumArchive/%3A">Pre-2004 Forum Archives</a></li>
</ul>

<h3>Search Tips</h3>
<ul>
<li>Click on one of the links above and type the search term after the URL in the search box</li>
<li>To enforce the search of a particular command, you may need to enclose it in quotes
(otherwise e.g. entering CharacterTable will also return results mentioning character tables)</li>
<li>
  Please note that GAP Forum Archives since December 2003 are not covered by the complete GAP website search,
  so you need to explicitly click on "GAP Forum Archives since December 2003" to search there
</li>
</ul>

